-- French Stocks Advance; Camaieu, Rallye, Saint-Gobain, Thales, Virbac Move
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2010-10-14T08:01:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/cap-gemini-casino-poncin-saint-gobain-rallye-french-equity-preview.html
France’s CAC 40 Index rose 0.2
percent to 3,837.49 as of 9:38 a.m. in Paris. The SBF 120 added
0.4 percent to 2,865.62.  The following shares rose or fell in Paris. Stock symbols
are in parentheses.  Camaieu  (AMA FP) gained 2.6 percent to 174.45 euros as the
designer of women’s clothing said third-quarter revenue rose 11
percent to 197.2 million euros ($275.3 million).  IMS International Metal Service  (IMS FP) rallied 7.1
percent to 12.86 euros as the metal distribution company said
its third-quarter sales rose to 275 million euros from 196
million euros.  Rallye SA  (RAL FP) rose 3.3 percent to 28.5 euros as the
holding company for supermarkets and other retail outlets said
sales rose 6.3 percent in the third quarter to 7.38 billion
euros.  Compagnie de Saint-Gobain  (SGO FP) climbed 2 percent to
35.24 euros. The glassmaker said it is starting the procedure
for a possible initial public offering of its packaging unit.
The unit had sales last year of 3.45 billion euros, the company
said.  Thales SA  (HO FP) gained 3.1 percent to 29.18 euros. The
company was upgraded to “buy” from “hold” at Societe
Generale SA.  Virbac SA  (VIRP FP) surged 5.1 percent to 114.5 euros. The
manufacturer of antibiotics said its third-quarter sales rose to
154 million euros from 122 million euros. The company forecast
sales growth of 8 percent to 10 percent in 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
